caption.title: List of model reactions.
caption.p: (A) The reaction-rate units are in 1/ms, 1/(nMms), 1/(nM2ms), 1/(nM3ms), or 1/(nM4ms), depending on the number of reactants. Reactions are grouped by similar modes of action and identical forward and backward rates. The denominators 𝐗, 𝐘, and 𝐙 represent groups of species detailed below. †: backward reaction rate proportional to [PKAc], not to [PKAc]2. (B) Groups of species as used in panel (A).

tr.td: 𝐗2 ∈ {LR, pLR, ppLR, pppLR, R, pR, ppR, pppR}
